scopecontent.p:
Spraker writes from 
         Fort Bragg, North Carolina; 
         Fort Meade; 
         Maryland; 
         New England; 
         Northern Ireland; 
         Luxembourg; 
         France; 
         Germany; 
         Czechoslovakia; and 
         Camp Campbell, Kentucky. In his letters
         he comments on army life, especially K. P. duty (July 23,
         1943) and family news, but for the most part, he assures his
         mother that he is well and safe. He mentions being disciplined
         for having returned late to his camp (June 1, 1943); makes
         reference to a visit by General 
         Dwight D. Eisenhowerto his camp June 4,
         1944); states that he is a member of General 
         George S. Patton, Jr.'s Third army
         (September 16, 1944); and mentions his being awarded a Silver
         Star (April 22, 1945); and his hope of being discharged
         quickly at the war's conclusion (August 20, 1945). Also
         present in the collection are two valentines, one of which is
         signed by Spraker.
